instructions.content:
BEAT EGG WHITES AND CREAM OF TARTAR UNTIL STIFF.  GRADUALLY ADD
SUGAR. FOLD IN CRUMBS AND NUTS.  POUR IN A LIGHTLY- BUTTERED PIE PAN;
BAKE AT 325 UNTIL SET, ABOUT 20 MIN. COOL.  TOP WITH COOL WHIP.

Preheat oven to 400.  Sprinkle salt and pepper evenly over chicken;
set aside.  Combine honey, mustard, paprika, and garlic powder in a
small bowl; stir well.  Combine cornflakes and pecans in a shallow
dish; stir well.  Brush both sides of chicken with honey mixture;
dredge in cornflake mixture.  Place chicken pieces on a large baking
sheet coated with cooking spray.  Lightly coat chicken with cooking
spray, and bake at 400 for 40 minutes or until done.

Calories 270 (30% from fat); Fat 8.9g (sat 1.7g, momo 3.9g, poly
2.6g); Protein 25g; Carb 21.4g; Fiber 0.5g; Chol 71mg; Iron 2mg;
Sodium 416mg; Calc 15mg
